The question is whether we can do better than this?

Linear Program Formulation
To evolve a linear programming formulation, first let's identify the decision variables.

Let ğ‘¥ğ‘–,ğ‘—
 denote the amount of material transported from source location ğ‘–
 to target location ğ‘—
. Since 0â‰¤ğ‘–â‰¤ğ‘›âˆ’1
 and 0â‰¤ğ‘—â‰¤ğ‘šâˆ’1
, there are ğ‘šÃ—ğ‘›
 such decision variables.

Clearly ğ‘¥ğ‘–,ğ‘—â‰¥0
 since it does not make any sense to transport negative amount of material.

Let ğ·ğ‘–,ğ‘—
 denote the distance from source location ğ‘–
 to destination location ğ‘—
.

ğ·ğ‘–,ğ‘—=(ğ‘¥ğ‘–âˆ’ğ‘¥â€²ğ‘—)2+(ğ‘¦ğ‘–âˆ’ğ‘¦â€²ğ‘—)2â¯â¯â¯â¯â¯â¯â¯â¯â¯â¯â¯â¯â¯â¯â¯â¯â¯â¯â¯â¯â¯â¯â¯â¯â¯â¯â¯â¯â¯â¯â¯â¯â¯â¯â¯âˆš.
